{{obsolete}}
{{Flavour|Instills a corruption within a target, temporarily mutating their body in an adverse fashion. It cannot affect artificial beings, and the undead will decompose if affected.}}

'''Corrupt Body''' is a monster-only spell which temporarily inflicts [[bad mutation]]s on its target, much like those caused by [[wretched star]]s. [[Mutation]] resistance prevents these as normal, and you can recover from them by gaining sufficient [[experience]]. [[Undead]] characters take [[stat]] damage instead of mutating, which can lead to rapid debilitation if you lack mutation resistance and fail to kill the spell's source quickly.

The following monsters can cast Corrupt Body:
*{{monsterlink|Corrupter}}

==History==
*In [[0.19]], this spell was removed.

